{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-16142].
  {panel}

Use case: User make a page in personal space and wants to convert\move the page into a news item (blog post) together with all attachments

Also want to move a blog post to a page.

Similar to the [Content by Label Macro|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/content-by-label-macro-145566.html], it would be nice to have a macro to list the topics - Questions for Confluence

h4. Workaround
To run the SQL command below.
{code}
SELECT CONTENTID, CONTENTTYPE, TITLE, CREATOR, CONTENT_STATUS 
FROM CONTENT
WHERE PLUGINKEY = 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-questions:topic-metadata';
{code} 

There is a bug - [CONFSERVER-47087 - Questions don't Appear in Content by Label Macro|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-47087], which causes topics to not be listed in Content by Label macro.
